President Obama has declared a major disaster in Delaware due to the effects of Hurricane Sandy. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Jack Schuback as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made based on future damage assessments.